               <p>1963. <persName id="def1-1963-18511027" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1963-18511027" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1963-18511027" type="age" value="19"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1963-18511027" type="surname" value="WILD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1963-18511027" type="given" value="JONATHAN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JONATHAN WILD</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18511027-1963-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18511027-1963-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18511027-1963-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>, unlawfully uttering counterfeit coin.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. SCRIVEN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">CLERK</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-802" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-802" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-802" type="surname" value="MEAD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-802" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN MEAD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am barmaid at the Bridge-house beer-shop, Old Kent-road. On 6th Sept., about half-past 8 o'clock in the evening, the pri<lb></lb>soner came and asked for a glass of gin—I told him we did not sell it, and he then said a glass of ale—I served him with it, and he threw down a half-crown—I tried it, bent it, and told him it was bad—he said he had just taken it of an omnibus conductor—he did not pay for the ale, but left without drinking it—I gave the half-crown to Pocock.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-803" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-803" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-803" type="surname" value="POCOCK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-803" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM POCOCK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am waster at the Briidge-house beer-shop. I remem<lb></lb>ber the prisoner coming on 8th Sept, and saw him give the half-crown to Mead—she gave it to me—I said to the prisoner, "This is a regular <hi rend="italic">duffer</hi>"—he said, "I was not aware of it; an omnibus conductor gave it me, a cousin of mine"—he wanted me to give it him back, but I would not; I gave it to Juniper—the prisoner left—I followed him, and saw him go to Mr. Simons's.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-804" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-804" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-804" type="surname" value="JUNIPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-804" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS JUNIPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in the beer-shop, and received the half-crown from Pocock—I melted it in the fire into two or three pieces, which I gave to the constable.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-805" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-805" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-805" type="surname" value="SIMONS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-805" type="given" value="JOHN HENRY"></interp>JOHN HENRY SIMONS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am assistant to Mr. Laydon, chemist, of the Old Kent-road. On 8th Sept the prisoner came for some salts, which came to 1 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he gave me a bad shilling in payment—I bent it, told him it was bad, and asked if he had any more—he said he was not aware it was bad—I gave</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185110270160"></xptr>
               <p>him into custody—I have examined two pieces of metal which were me by a constable; they are not silver.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-806" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-806" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-806" type="surname" value="THOROGOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-806" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN THOROGOOD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, P</hi> 180). I received the prisoner in custody at Mr. Simons's shop, and received this shilling from him, and these two pieces I received from a constable of the M division, to whom I had seen Juniper give them (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-807" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-807" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-807" type="surname" value="WEBSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-807" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEBSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. This shilling is counterfeit, and these are pieces of the same metal.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I had the money in change for a half-sovereign; I was drunk.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18511027-name-808" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-808" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-808" type="surname" value="THOROGOOD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18511027-name-808" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN THOROGOOD</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I found no other money on him—he pretended to be drunk, but I do not think he was.</p>
